ActIndian Act
SubjectObushkudayang Indian Reserve, Manitoba ** Creation **
PrecisOrder setting apart 321.83 hectares (795.26 acres) of lands, including mines and minerals, for the use and benefit of the Lake St. Martin First Nation as creation of OBUSHKUDAYANG INDIAN RESERVE, located in the Rural Municipality of Grahamdale at approximately from the Town of Gypsumville, Manitoba.
